The origin of the name Gowen County is unknown at this time.

Gowen County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located to the east of the Castlereagh River in the area to the east of Gilgandra , to Coonabarabran in the north-east. This includes land on both sides of the Newell Highway .
